## 4. PROJECT KICKOFF — 6 docs before you write any code (Source 5)

> "Even before writing a single line of code, here are six documents you should
> have." These give the AI agent the context to build correctly instead of
> guessing. Write them with Claude/ChatGPT, keep them in the repo (e.g. `/docs`),
> and reference them when scaffolding. Do this at the start of every NEW project.

1. **PRD — Product Requirements Document**
   - Brief overview of the whole app idea + every feature, exactly what you're building.
2. **TRD — Technical Requirements Document**
   - All tech decisions: stack, tools, APIs. The blueprint so the agent makes
     technical choices without guessing.
3. **App Flow**
   - Every screen/piece, navigation, full user journey: what happens when a user
     taps a button, which page it goes to, etc.
4. **UI/UX Design Brief**
   - Look and feel: color palette, typography, components, style, and roughly how
     each screen should look — so the AI doesn't build something random.
5. **Backend Schema**
   - How user data is stored/organized: full auth flow, every table with its
     columns and relationships. (Pair with Section 1.2 RLS + Section 2 cost rules.)
6. **Implementation Plan**
   - Exact step-by-step build sequence so the agent builds in the right order.

### Kickoff ship-gate (new projects)
1. `/docs/PRD.md`, `TRD.md`, `APP_FLOW.md`, `UIUX_BRIEF.md`, `BACKEND_SCHEMA.md`,
   `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md` exist and are filled in.
2. Schema doc designed with RLS + efficient-query rules already in mind.
3. Implementation plan ordered so auth/security land before feature sprawl.

