## 6. SOCIAL DISTRIBUTION — post to win the 2026 algorithms (added 2026-07-09)

> Learned from 2026 platform-algorithm guides (Hootsuite, Sprout, Later, Buffer,
> Sprout/SocialPilot, LinkedIn deep-dives, Postory/Monolit for Threads, Reddit
> self-promo guides). Applied to PALM's Jul 13–Aug 9 plan + Thu/Fri gap posts.

### Cross-platform truths (all of Meta + LinkedIn)
- [ ] **Saves + sends (DM shares) now beat likes** everywhere. Design posts people
      *bookmark* or *send to a coworker* ("tag someone who…", itemized/checklist/
      how-to formats). Likes are the weakest signal in 2026.
- [ ] **Substantive comments > reactions.** End every post with ONE specific,
      answerable question. Threads with 4+ back-and-forth replies get big reach
      boosts (FB cites up to +300%).
- [ ] **The first 30–60 min decide reach.** Be present in the golden hour: reply to
      every comment fast (that reply is a fresh engagement event and extends the
      scoring window). Don't post-and-leave.
- [ ] **Originality wins; reposts are penalized.** Meta/IG demote aggregator/reposted
      content and can swap in the original. Our in-house creative studio (real logo,
      real app screens) is the right approach — never fake logos or stock-look AI.
- [ ] **Niche consistency** so the interest model can classify the account: stay on
      home-care/agency-ops topics; occasional off-topic is fine, scattered is not.
- [ ] **Engagement bait is down-ranked** ("like if you agree", "comment YES"). Ask a
      *real* question instead.

### Instagram / Facebook (Meta)
- [ ] **Video = Reels = the discovery engine.** ~50% of feed is now recommended
      (non-followers). Static/carousel still work in-feed, but short vertical video
      (hook in 3s, on-screen captions, aim 50% mid-video retention) reaches new people.
- [ ] **SEO over hashtags:** put the searched keyword phrase in the FIRST line of the
      caption + profile; use 3–5 niche hashtags, not big stacks. Add alt text.
- [ ] **Stories daily** with polls/questions/quizzes; repost feed posts to Story
      (Story views count toward Reel views). Link stays in bio for IG.
- [ ] Post 1–2×/day, consistent cadence > bursts.

### Threads
- [ ] **Replies outrank likes ~10×; engagement velocity in the first hour is the #1
      signal.** Write conversational, personal, opinion/hot-take posts (not brand copy).
- [ ] **Keep links OUT of the post body** (in-body links suppress reach) — put the link
      in your own **first reply**. Post 5–7×/week; reply to every reply with substance.
- [ ] Activate the IG audience; spend 10–15 min/day replying on other niche accounts.

### LinkedIn — 2026 "Authenticity Update" (BIG CHANGE)
- [ ] **Depth Score rules:** dwell time + saves + substantive comments, read by an LLM
      that scores original insight. Surface-level/reshared content is throttled.
- [ ] **⚠️ The link-in-first-comment trick is now PENALIZED too** (was our plan's default).
      External links in body OR first comment cut reach 50–80%. New rule: **deliver full
      value in the post, keep the URL on the image/in bio**, or accept the trade-off.
      (Our poster still supports a first-comment link, but prefer link-free.)
- [ ] **Document carousels (PDF) + multi-image carousels = highest dwell time** → best
      reach. Hook <140 chars, short 1–3 sentence paragraphs, then deliver.
- [ ] 2–4 posts/week (quality > volume); comment on others' posts 10–15 min BEFORE you
      post (highest-ROI activity); reply to every comment within the golden hour.

### Reddit (and it feeds Google + LLM answers)
- [ ] **9:1 (better 19:1) rule:** ≤10% of activity self-promotional. Age the account,
      earn karma first, read each subreddit's rules, use the sanctioned "Show/Feedback"
      threads.
- [ ] **Reply-marketing > link posts:** answer the person's question, disclose you built
      it ("full disclosure, I made this"), mention the product as one option, often skip
      the link entirely (people Google the name; links raise spam-filter risk).
- [ ] No sales jargon ("revolutionary/game-changing"); no multi-account voting (perma-ban).

